name: $::type
desc: Returns: Precusory content structure and use, i.e., a boilerplate, template, application for a contract such as an insurance policy or benefits under a program, e.g., workers compensation.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Precusory content structure and use, i.e., a boilerplate, template, application for a contract such as an insurance policy or benefits under a program, e.g., workers compensation.

name: $publisher
desc: Returns: The  individual or organization that published the Contract precursor content.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The  individual or organization that published the Contract precursor content.

name: $publicationDate
desc: Returns: The date (and optionally time) when the contract was published. The date must change when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the contract changes.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The date (and optionally time) when the contract was published. The date must change when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the contract changes.

name: $publicationStatus
desc: Returns: amended | appended | cancelled | disputed | entered-in-error | executable | executed | negotiable | offered | policy | rejected | renewed | revoked | resolved | terminated.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: amended | appended | cancelled | disputed | entered-in-error | executable | executed | negotiable | offered | policy | rejected | renewed | revoked | resolved | terminated.

name: $copyright
desc: Returns: A copyright statement relating to Contract precursor content. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the Contract precursor content.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A copyright statement relating to Contract precursor content. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the Contract precursor content.
